                <div class='_separate-5'>
                    <h3 class='_bigger-2' id='components'>Components</h3>

                    <p class='mui-p _separate-1'>Muilessium has a number of components listed below. Every component has a markup shown in example and this markup should be used as is, because some initializations of components are based on their markups.</p>

                    {{#files}}
                        <div id='{{file}}' class='_allow-empty'></div>
                        {{#blocks }}
                            <div class='_separate-5'>
                                <h4 class='_bigger-1'>{{ name }}</h4>
                                <div class='_smaller-2 -grey-4'>{{ ../file }}</div>
                                {{#if description }}
                                    <p class='mui-p _separate-1'>{{ description }}</p>
                                {{/if}}
                                {{#depends }}
                                    <div class='_smaller-2 -blue-4'>Depends on {{ depends }}</div>
                                {{/depends}}
                                {{#requires}}
                                    <div class='_smaller-2 -red-4'>Requires {{ requires }}</div>
                                {{/requires}}
                                {{#if markup}}
                                    <div class='_separate-1'>
                                        <div class='example _separate-2'>{{{ markup.example }}}</div>
                                        {{#state}}
                                            <div class='state _separate-2'>
                                                <h5 class='_smaller-1'>{{ ../../name }} with {{name}} option</h5>
                                                <div class='example _separate-2' data-class='{{name}}'>{{{ ../markup.example }}}</div>
                                            </div>
                                        {{/state}}
                                        <div class='code _separate-2 _smaller-2'>
                                            <pre class='( prettyprint lang-html )'>{{{markup.escaped}}}</pre>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                {{/if}}
                            </div>
                        {{/blocks}}
                    {{/files}}
                </div>




                <div class='_separate-5'>
                    <h3 class='_bigger-2' id="faq">F.A.Q.</h3>

                    <div class='questions-list _separate-1'>
                        <div class='_separate-1'>
                            <div class='question'>Can I use Muilessium in my project?</div>
                            <div class='answer'>Yes, Muilessium is distributed under the MIT license, so You can use it in Your projects.</div>
                        </div>

                        <div class='_separate-1'>
                            <div class='question'>What browsers are supported?</div>
                            <div class='answer'>All modern browsers, including IE11.</div>
                        </div>
                        
                        <div class='_separate-1'>
                            <div class='question'>Who is the author?</div>
                            <div class='answer'>My name is Ivan Bogachev. I'm a musitian and front-end developer, You could see <a href='http://codepen.io/sfi0zy/'>some of my pens on codepen</a> previously.</div>
                        </div>

                        <div class='_separate-1'>
                            <div class='question'>I found a bug?</div>
                            <div class='answer'>If you found a bug - don't worry, Muilessium is not officially released yet and can have some bugs, You can open an issue on <a href='https://github.com/sfi0zy/muilessium'>GitHub</a> or send me an <a href='mailto:sfi0zy@gmail.com'>email</a> and I will fix a problem when I will have a time.</div>
                        </div>

                        <div class='_separate-1'>
                            <div class='question'>I have some suggestions for improvement of Muilessium</div>
                            <div class='answer'>That's great! You can fork Muilesssium, add Your functionality and create a pull request, or contact with me by <a href='mailto:sfi0zy@gmail.com'>email</a> or <a href='https://twitter.com/sfi0zy'>twitter</a> (but I should  notify You - English is not my native language, maybe I'll need some time to translate messages)</div>
                        </div>
